VSangita Kalanidhis: Gaambhirya Sangita Pravaham &#8211; Vols &#8211; 1 &amp; 2CD: Sa Re Ga Ma, Price: Rs. 175The two-volume album boasts samples by 14 Carnatic greats. Vol 1 has veterans including Ariyakkudi, Chembai, Semmangudi, GNB, Madurai Mani Iyer, Maharajapuram Viswanatha Iyer, Alathur Brothers and Balamuralikrishna singing one kriti each. Vol 2 has K.V. Narayanaswamy, B. Rajam Iyer, Maharajapuram Santhanam, D.K. Jayaraman, T.V. Sankaranarayanan and T.N. Seshagopalan. One hopes  great names such as &#8216;Flute&#8217; Mali, D.K. Pattammal and M.S. Subbulakshmi, to name a few, will be included in the subsequent editions.  The two volumes whet your musical appetite and are ideal for those who are just beginning to enjoy Carnatic music.T.N. Krishnan &amp; Sriram Krishnan; Violin DuetCD: Sa Re Ga Ma; Price: Rs. 150.In this album, the father-son duo tackles ragas including Kharaharapriya (&#8216;Pakkala Nilabadi&#8217;), Behag (&#8216;Oruthi Maganaai&#8217;) and Suruti (&#8216;Sri Venkata Gireesam&#8217;) with traditional fervour. Krishnan is known for his soulful and melodious bowing. That son Sriram is following suit and continuing a family tradition with panache is evident in this album. The accompanists are Thiruvavur Bhaktavatsalam (mridangam), Vaikom Gopalakrishnan (ghatam) and Srirangam Kannan (morsing).Carnatic in Sitar: B. Sivaramakrishna RaoCD: Sa Re Ga Ma; Price: Rs. 150Sivaramakrishna Rao, a disciple of Pt. Subba Rao and Ustad Ahmed Hussain Khan, attempts to create Carnatic magic on a  Hindustani instrument. The choice of ragas includes Bangala (&#8216;Girirajasutha Tanaya&#8217;), Naatai (&#8216;Jagadananda Karaka&#8217;), Vasantha (&#8216;Seethamma Maayamma&#8217;) and a Madhuvanti thillana. The rhythms have been arranged by ganjira expert Selva Ganesh and N. Ramakrishnan, with support from Saindhavi (vocal), B.V. Balasai (flute), Durga Prasad (gottuvadhyam), B.V. Raghavendra Rao, C.H. Eshwar (keyboards), Ramakrishna (mridangam), Uma Shankar Vinayakram (ghatam) and B. Ganesh Rao (tabla). Worth listening.Bal HanumanDVD; English;Geetanjali (Super Audio);  Price: Rs. 300.The endearing character of Hanuman, the monkey warrior, comes alive in this animated version. The story of Hanuman&#8217;s birth and his happy childhood filled with innocent pranks &#8211; his reaching out to the Sun and childhood sports &#8211; keep the viewers engaged. The one-hour DVD is a great way to introduce children to the legend of Hanuman.
